'''Evann Ludovic Vidjannagni Guessand''' (born 1 July 2001) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] or [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]], on loan from [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]]. Born in France, he represents the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].

Guessand is a product of the [[OGC Nice|Nice]] academy, and progressed through their youth and B sides to the first team, before transferring to Aston Villa in 2025. He also spent time on loan at [[FC Lausanne-Sport|Lausanne-Sport]] and [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] earlier in his career.

Guessand was a regular French youth international up to [[France national under-19 football team|under-19]] level, before switching to the Ivory Coast in 2024.

==Early life==
Evann Ludovic Vidjannagni Guessand<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4407896/202526-premier-league-squad-lists |title=2025/26 Premier League squad lists |publisher=Premier League |date=12 September 2025 |access-date=1 February 2026}}</ref> was born on 1 July 2001 in [[Ajaccio]], Corse-du-Sud.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur69899.html |title=Evann Guessand |newspaper=L'Équipe |location=Paris |access-date=1 February 2026 |language=fr}}</ref> His father Servais Guessand Konan is an Ivorian former footballer who played professionally for [[AC Ajaccio]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/ogc-nice/un-melange-de-bafetimbi-gomis-et-mamadou-niang-un-genie-evann-guessand-enfin-le-bon-elan-e496582a-e21a-11ef-822c-d93b68cf46e7|title=« Un mélange de Bafétimbi Gomis et Mamadou Niang… un génie » : Evann Guessand, enfin le bon élan ?|language=French|date=1 March 2025|access-date=5 March 2026|website=Ouest France}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Nice===
Guessand joined the youth academy of [[OGC Nice]] at the age of 12.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20250808-l-international-ivoirien-evann-guessand-quitte-nice-pour-aston-villa|title=L'international ivoirien Evann Guessand quitte Nice pour Aston Villa|language=French|date=8 August 2025|access-date=5 March 2026|website=RFI}}</ref> On 5 January 2020, he made his professional debut in a 2–0 [[Coupe de France]] win over [[ÉFC Fréjus Saint-Raphaël|Fréjus Saint-Raphaël]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bacquié |first=Maxime |date=5 January 2020 |title=Coupe de France : OGC Nice / Fréjus-Saint-Raphaël |url=https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/coupe-de-france-vivez-ogc-nice-frejus-saint-raphael-sur-france-bleu-azur-1578222943 |archive-url= |archive-date= |access-date=23 August 2020 |website=[[France Bleu]] |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Coupe de France : l'OGC Nice bat l'Etoile FC Fréjus St Raphaël 2 à 0 |url=https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/provence-alpes-cote-d-azur/nice-ogc-nice-rencontre-etoile-fc-frejus-st-raphael-17-heures-1770103.html |access-date=23 August 2020 |website=France 3 Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur |date=May 2020 |language=fr-FR}}</ref> On 23 August, he made his [[Ligue 1]] debut against [[RC Lens|Lens]] as a late substitute in 2–1 home win.<ref>{{Cite web |title=OGC Nice – RC Lens match details |url=https://www.tntsports.co.uk/football/ligue-1/2020-2021/live-ogc-nice-rc-lens_mtc1191559/live.shtml |access-date=8 July 2025 |website=tntsports.co.uk |date=23 August 2020 |language=en}}</ref>

====Loan to Lausanne====
On 30 September 2020, Guessand joined [[FC Lausanne-Sport]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-lucas-da-cunha-quitte-rennes-pour-nice-avant-de-partir-en-pret-a-lausanne/1177967|title=Transferts : Lucas Da Cunha quitte Rennes pour Nice avant de partir en prêt à Lausanne|date=30 September 2020|access-date=5 March 2026|language=French|website=L'Équipe}}</ref> On 3 October, he made his [[Swiss Super League]] debut against [[FC Zürich|Zürich]], scoring his first goal for the club in the 4–0 home victory.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Lausanne-Sport – FC Zürich match details |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/10/03/switzerland/super-league/fc-lausanne-sport/fc-zurich/3361615/ |access-date=8 July 2025 |website=soccerway.com |date=3 October 2020 |language=en}}</ref> In total, he scored seven goals during the [[2020–21 Swiss Super League|2020–21 season]], making him the team's top goalscorer, and also recorded five assists.<ref name=contract>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Evann-guessand-prolonge-a-l-ogc-nice-jusqu-en-2026/1273704|title=Evann Guessand prolonge à l'OGC Nice jusqu'en 2026|language=French|date=27 July 2021|access-date=5 March 2026|website=L'Équipe}}</ref>

====Return to Nice====
In the pre-season of [[2021–22 OGC Nice season|2021–22]], Guessand extended his contract at Nice until 2026.<ref name=contract/> On 24 October 2021, he recorded his first goal for the club, scoring a stoppage time winner against [[Olympique Lyonnais]] after coming on as an 83rd minute substitute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rfi.fr/en/sports/20211024-nice-youngster-guessand-claims-late-win-over-10-man-lyon|title=Nice youngster Guessand claims late win over 10-man Lyon|language=French|date=24 October 2021|access-date=5 March 2026|website=RFI}}</ref> Three days later, he made his first start in a 1–1 draw against [[Olympique de Marseille]], assisting a goal for [[Amine Gouiri]] six minutes into the Mediterranean derby.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ogcnice.com/en/resume/119587/a-derby-without-a-winner-1-1.html|title=A derby without a winner (1-1)|date=27 October 2021|access-date=5 March 2026|website=OGC Nice}}</ref>

Overall, he made 20 league appearances during the season, including two starts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ogcnice.com/fr/article/121804/evann-guessand-prete-a-nantes.html|title=Evann Guessand prêté à Nantes|language=French|date=12 July 2022|access-date=5 March 2026|website=OGC Nice}}</ref> In the [[2021–22 Coupe de France]], Guessand made substitute appearances in every round, including the [[2022 Coupe de France final]] where Nice were beaten 1–0 by [[FC Nantes]] at the [[Stade de France]] on 7 May.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/coupe-de-france/2021-2022/nice-nantes-live/530190|title=Nice 0-1 Nantes, Coupe de France, résultat et résumé du match (07/05/2022)|date=7 May 2022|access-date=5 March 2026|website=L'Équipe}}</ref>

====Loan to Nantes====
On 12 July 2022, Guessand joined [[Ligue 1]] club Nantes on a season-long loan.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 July 2022 |title=Evann Guessand prêté au FC Nantes ! |trans-title=Evann Guessand loaned to Nantes! |url=https://www.fcnantes.com/articles/article2809.php?num=40370 |access-date=12 July 2022 |publisher=[[FC Nantes]] |language=fr}}</ref> He made his debut for the club in the [[2022 Trophée des Champions]] on 31 July, where they were beaten 4–0 by [[Paris Saint-Germain]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/sport/article/2022/07/31/football-face-a-nantes-le-psg-decroche-son-onzieme-trophee-des-champions_6136777_3242.html|title=Football : face à Nantes, le PSG décroche son onzième Trophée des champions|language=French|date=31 July 2022|access-date=5 March 2026|website=Le Monde}}</ref>

He scored his first goal for the club in a 3–1 league win over [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]] on 28 August.<ref>{{Cite web |date=28 August 2022 |title=Nantes vs. Toulouse |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/08/28/france/ligue-1/fc-nantes/toulouse-fc/3802173/ |access-date=9 September 2022 |website=Soccerway}}</ref> On 8 September, on his [[UEFA Europa League]] debut, Guessand scored the winning goal for Nantes in the final minutes of a 2–1 home victory over [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 September 2022 |title=FC Nantes. Evann Guessand : « C'était une ambiance de fous » |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/fc-nantes/fc-nantes-evann-guessand-c-etait-une-ambiance-de-fous-bfb62d0e-2fc6-11ed-bd84-c332a9af669a |access-date=9 September 2022 |website=[[Ouest-France]] |language=fr}}</ref>

Guessand ended 2022–23 as a runner-up in the [[2022–23 Coupe de France|Coupe de France]] for the second consecutive season. He was an unused substitute in the [[2023 Coupe de France final]] on 29 April, where Nantes were beaten 5–1 by [[FC Toulouse]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65439267|title=Nantes 1-5 Toulouse: Toulouse win first major trophy in French Cup final|date=29 April 2023|access-date=5 March 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

====Second return to Nice====
Guessand appeared in all 34 of Nice's matches in the [[2023–24 Ligue 1]] season, starting in 14 matches and scoring six goals.<ref name=stats>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/player/stats/_/id/288924/team/2502|title=Evann Guessand Career Stats - Ligue 1 - ESPN (AU)|access-date=5 March 2026|website=ESPN}}</ref> In [[2024–25 Ligue 1|2024–25]], he was named the club's Player of the Season<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c0mk7wr18kxo|title=Crystal Palace sign Villa forward Guessand on loan|date=30 January 2026|access-date=5 March 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> after scoring twelve goals and recording nine assists.<ref name=stats/>

===Aston Villa===
On 8 August 2025, Guessand signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] for an undisclosed fee; the contract is valid until 2030.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=8 August 2025 |title=Villa announce Evann Guessand signing |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2025/august/08/villa-announce-evann-guessand-signing/ |access-date=8 August 2025 |website=Aston Villa Football Club}}</ref> This fee was reported to be worth €35 million (£30.5 million).<ref>{{Cite web |last=Veal |first=Jonathan |date=7 August 2025 |title=Evann Guessand Aston Villa medical update as final transfer fee emerges |url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/evann-guessand-aston-villa-medical-32215842.amp |access-date=8 August 2025 |website=Birmingham Live}}</ref> He made his Premier League debut as a late substitute in a 1–0 defeat to [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] on 23 August.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Brentford v Aston Villa {{!}} 2025/2026 {{!}} Premier League {{!}} Overview |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/match/2561907/brentford-vs-aston-villa |access-date=2025-08-23 |website=www.premierleague.com |language=en}}</ref> On 23 October, Guessand scored his first Aston Villa goal in an eventual 2–1 Europa League defeat to [[Go Ahead Eagles]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 October 2025 |title=Go Ahead Eagles vs Aston Villa {{!}} UEFA Europa League 2025/26 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2046206--go-ahead-eagles-vs-aston-villa/ |access-date=2025-10-23 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref>

==== Loan to Crystal Palace ====
On 30 January 2026, Guessand joined fellow Premier League club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] on a loan deal, with an option to make the move permanent at the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Evann Guessand transfer: Crystal Palace sign Aston Villa forward on loan|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c0mk7wr18kxo|website=BBC Sport|date=30 January 2026|access-date=31 January 2026|language=en-GB}}</ref> He made his debut on 8 February as a second-half substitute away at [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.–Crystal Palace F.C. rivalry|rivals]] [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]], contributing with an assist for [[Ismaïla Sarr]] to ensure a 1–0 victory for Palace and end a 12-match winless streak.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Premier League LIVE: Crystal Palace beat Brighton to end winless run |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c0410xkr72wt |access-date=2026-02-27 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 22 February, he scored his first goal for Crystal Palace and first goal in the Premier League, a 90th-minute winner to seal a 1–0 victory against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Crystal Palace 1-0 Wolves: Late Guessand strike gives Palace win over 10-man Wolves |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cp81ldpd65xt |access-date=2026-02-27 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Four days later, he scored Palace's second goal in the 2–0 win over [[HŠK Zrinjski Mostar]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Conference League|UEFA Conference League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cx2rvjqdw2kt|title=Crystal Palace 2–0 Zrinjski (3-1 agg): Palace reach last 16 of Conference League|date=26 February 2026|access-date=5 March 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

Guessand concluded the 2025–26 season with two European titles, having featured in the [[Europa League-winning Aston Villa squad]] and the Conference League-winning Crystal Palace side.<ref>{{cite web |last=Prince |first=Toby |url=https://tribuna.com/en/blogs/two-trophies-one-season-evann-guessand-makes-history-by-winn/ |title=Two trophies, one season: Evann Guessand makes history by winning Europa and Conference League |publisher=Tribuna.com |date=27 May 2026 }}</ref>

The  option-to-buy Evann Guessand expired on 1 June 2026.<ref>https://readastonvilla.com/2026/06/01/aston-villas-evann-guessand-weighing-up-future-after-crystal-palace-buy-option-expires/</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, Guessand holds French and Ivorian nationalities.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.unfp.org/joueur/evann-guessand-21987/ | title=Evann GUESSAND – }}</ref> After representing France at youth level,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.lausanne-sport.ch/je-sens-un-groupe-qui-vit-bien-ensemble/ |title="JE SENS UN GROUPE QUI VIT BIEN ENSEMBLE!" |date=23 October 2020}}</ref> Guessand was named in the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]]'s provisional squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] in December 2023.<ref>{{cite web |title=AFCON 2023 – PROVISIONAL SQUADS LIST|url=https://www.cafonline.com/media/szzh20fx/afcon-2023-provisional-squads-list.pdf|page=13}}</ref>

Guessand made his debut for the Ivory Coast national team on 11 June 2024 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF Group F|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Kenya national football team|Kenya]] at the [[Bingu National Stadium]] in Lilongwe, Malawi. He substituted [[Emmanuel Latte Lath]] in the 61st minute of a scoreless draw.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/687266/|title=Kenya v Ivory Coast game report|date=11 June 2024}}</ref> He scored his first international goal in a 1–0 win over [[Burundi national football team|Burundi]] on 21 March 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/tv/replay/le-but-d-evann-guessand-avec-la-cote-d-ivoire/20207153|title=Le but d'Evann Guessand avec la Côte d'Ivoire|language=French|date=21 March 2025|access-date=5 March 2026|website=L'Équipe}}</ref>

Having originally only named in the back-up squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]], Guessand was called up to the tournament squad to replace the injured [[Sébastien Haller]] on 19 December 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 December 2025 |title=Aston Villa News: Evann Guessand joins Ivory Coast squad |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c20g2l5e4qlo |access-date=29 December 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He appeared in four of the team's five matches at the tournament, scoring once in a 3–2 win over [[Gabon national football team|Gabon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c0je0xzg3zvt|title=Afcon 2025: Gabon 2-3 Ivory Coast: Elephants top group on goal difference|date=31 December 2025|access-date=5 March 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

On May 15, 2026, Guessand was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Faé]] in his list of 26 players in order to participate in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

==Personal life==
Guessand is the older brother of [[Axel Guessand]], who is also a former French youth international footballer.<ref name="c426">{{cite web | last=Trésarrieu | first=Flavien | title=Transferts : l'Udinese vise Axel Guessand (Nancy) | website=L&#x27;Équipe | date=2022-06-22 | url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-l-udinese-vise-axel-guessand-nancy/1339799 | language=fr | access-date=2025-03-27}}</ref>

